<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="831" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1344</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            American Representative on the United Nations War Grimes Commission</hi>
                            (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Pell</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 8</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-18">March 18,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of your despatch
                        no. 14144 dated February 29, 1944 concerning the discussion of an
                        international enforcement organization at the meeting of the Committee on
                        Means of Enforcement on February 25. Apparently your despatch and the
                        Department’s instruction no. 6 dated February 15, 1944 crossed in the mails.
                        The instruction referred to summarizes the Department’s tentative views on
                        the subject.</p>
                    <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>